  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To analyse and describe sinus microbiota, during hard to treat (or refractory)
      rhinosinusitis, using culturomic and metagenomic methods (i.e. to culture on many different
      medium of culture to grow hard to cultivate bacteria + to sequence and analyse all DNA
      contained in samples).

      Samples are middle meatus swabs or pus aspiration, done during usually patient following.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
